EXCELLENT SERVICE AND AMAZING FOOD! My parents had an out-of-this-world pizza at Grotto a few years back, and when we went to visit again this Feb, we made our way over so I could try it. Unfortunately, it wasn't on the menu at that time. The host, Neil, went above and beyond, and offered to ask the chef if he would make it especially for us. The next day, we had it for dinner, and it lived up to every expectation. Our server, Taya, was also excellent, recommended unique and tasty drinks and food. We left very satisfied and full. I would recommend Grotto to absolutely everyone, definitely worth checking out! Thank you Neil and Taya for making our experience unforgettable!

**updated 2/24/2020  The restaurant has been moved. It’s much smaller but the quality is still amazing. Other thing I would improve is having staff members (girl in a white coat with sleeve tattoos) should not reach across people eating to grab an empty plate in middle of dinner. 3 1/2 Stars:  Wanted pasta so we made reservations on a Saturday.  The restaurant was busy but there were a few tables open.  Service was ok. We had to ask a few times for water.  No one was actually walking around and filling glasses as needed. We had waved our server down.  Food: Carbonara- There was a fried egg on it which I prefer a runny yolk to mix in the pasta. In addition I prefer pancetta which there were a few pieces but my dish was topped with bacon bits. Not the worse carbonara I've ever had and not the best either. Bolognese with Angel Hair pasta- this was delicious.  Great balance of flavors.  Restaurant was nice and clean but would only return for the complimentary bread (because of the olive oil dipping sauce)  and Bolognese.

Delicious! This is a cute little restaurant in the Golden Nugget, it's very charming and attractive but not at all pretentious. My party of 6 came in around 8:30 last Saturday night (it was busy, but we only waited 10 mins without a reservation) and everyone was very impressed with their meal. While we waited, the host gave us some great tips on which bars to go to after dinner. I had a shrimp pasta with grilled shrimp and the best sauce I've ever had, plus my plate was decorated with edible flowers. I couldn't believe my entree was only $22! My boyfriend had the short rib gnocci with melt-in-your-mouth meat, and my friend had their lasagna which was so unique (like a personal lasagna, not one cut from a pan) and she absolutely loved it. Two of our friends ordered pizzas and they looked tasty; they ordered the thick crust but it still looked pretty thin to me so I'm guessing the thin crust is probably more like a cracker/flatbread. Our server was delightful. I would definitely go back!
Veal kickeeillo was the worst veal I have had in my life. Pressed too thin, breading was tasteless, lemon sauce too strong and the portion sparse. Server was very polite and timely.

Located in The Venetian in The Strip, Yardbird Southern Table and Bar is a great place for dinner!  They have a laid back vibe, and some great food!  You can order things family style or individually- the serving sizes are enough to share.  I've had a lot of fried chicken, but was really pleasantly surprised at how good the fried chicken is here!  Crispy outside and very moist and perfectly cooked inside!  They also have some great sauces that can enhance the chicken, the cornbread and even the cake!  Definitely a place you need reservations for - so plan accordingly!

We found out about 15min later that in order to get parking validated you needed a copy of the receipt from the restaurant. We had not taken our receipt and went back to get it. We asked the bartender if we could get it and he informed us that since it was rung in by a different person it wasn’t possible. It had not been more than 15 min at that point. I work in casinos in Vegas and know how easily it is to either pull the customer copy off the top of the trash or call a manager to reprint the copy. It takes a couple minutes at the most. As one of the sit down restaurants in the casino they know that people need receipts to get parking validated. The response was uncaring and again could have been handled much better.

While wandering around outside, we found out that there are many restaurants inside the Golden Nugget, our hotel! And oh man it was a good choice to eat at Grotto. My girlfriend and I split a pasta dish, but she is vegetarian so she ordered without the ham. They sent out our food on two separate dishes (very well done, a touch not many restaurants hit on.). Mine had ham, which I didn't mind, but hers had bacon it looked like. I guess we should've specified she's vegetarian, oh well. We had to have them sent back (sorry). They were quick at sending new dishes out.  Oh man was it ever good!! Absolutely delicious pasta! Amazing. Sharing was just the right portion. The servings arent huge per other places, they're just right if you're hungry. Quality over quantity!  The dessert was also very enticing and delicious. I hear they make some award winning stuff, and after tasting it I know why! This place is awesome.  Our waiter was also the best, a guy with real character. He was very funny, not trying to be someone he wasn't.  Very awesome eatery.

My husband is always ready for Italian food. We have ate at many Italian restaurants. We ended up in Fremont Street our last night in Vegas and knowing he hadn’t had the chance at Italian yet, we made our way to the grotto. It was kind of later in the evening, not super busy. We enjoyed watching the guys make pizza near our table. We ordered the Calamari for an app, it was most likely the best we’ve ever had! My husband is a ranch fanatic, and we hadn’t asked for any, he gladly dipped his calamari in the marinara and said it was the best he had had before. I was not very hungry so we decided to split an entree, I can’t remember exactly what it was but some fish plate with asparagus and potatoes. The staff even split it up prior to bringing it to our table! Very good! I wish I hadn’t ate lunch that day so we could have tried more from the menu!
